    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In biology, a modification of a protein’s structure brought about by heat, alkalis, and other factors, which causes it to collapse into a disordered mass. The process Is irreversible for most proteins. In conservation science, the denaturation of leather and parchment is studied by various analytical techniques.  </Note_Text>
